DIY WALKWAY: Before the days of stories and reels, I decided to DIY my walkway. I found tumbled marble cobblestone for pennies on the dollar at a local rock yard. This kind of stone is not very common or sought after in Florida but it was perfect to me and reminded me so much of my northern roots. Although the house was purchased in 2013, the real work started in 2015 and continues until today. Just a month ago, irrigation and sod was installed. When people ask why it’s taken close to a decade to fix up my fixer, my response is “home takes time”! What do you think? Are you feeling the walkway and transformation?

Okay, confession, my pool fountain was pretty from afar but far from pretty. I neglected it for far too long and allowed it to naturally “weather”, aka get grimy! I also never added anything to the planter portion of the fountain so I decided to give it a bit of  a makeover. I gave it a deep cleaning using @30secondscleaners . It was really easy to use. I attached it to my hose, sprayed my fountain, let it sit for a few minutes and then hosed everything off. I couldn’t believe how pretty the rock was underneath. You may have beauty waiting to be unearthed that just needs a little love. If so, be sure to use 30 Seconds Outdoor Cleaner. #ad

The flowers from my dad’s memorial service were at various stages of wilting. Instead of throwing them away, I decided to combine them and create this wreath in his memory. A reminder that we are are all at various stages of life but still beautiful. I found an extendable hook that was heavy enough to support the weight of the wreath and pretty pillow covers that complemented the flower colors. If you’re interested in either, comment “shop” and I will send you the link. 

#cottagehome #cottagecorehome #griefawareness #griefjourney #porchdecor #frontporch

It is with a heavy heart that I announce the passing of my dad Willie. Many of you may remember I’ve shared his battle with dementia in my stories over the last few years. Willie married my mom when she was raising, my brother, sister and I alone. He stepped in and provided us spiritually, emotionally and physically with a life we would not have had otherwise. 🥹 He was always such a strong, vibrant man and the picture of health. When he gave me away he was 58 years old but looked 30. He was diagnosed with mild dementia in 2019 but contracted Covid in 2020 and began to rapidly decline, the last three years being the worse. I will miss his smile, his kindness and zest for life. He will be forever loved. 💔

#dementia #dementiawareness #dementiasucks

Remember my Outdoor Canopy Chair Makeover? What I didn’t share before was how utterly gross the cushions were. I didn’t cover them last year and from the looks of them, I thought they were a goner. I discovered @30secondscleaners and was excited to see that the product was safe to use on canvas in addition to siding, stucco, wood and other surfaces. I sprayed the cleaner on and my cushions were brought back to life! I LOOOOVE this cleaner and can’t wait to use it again!
